# RecapFlow VM-side daily snapshot — user crontab entry.
# Install with: crontab -e
# Then paste the line below (uncommented):
#
# 0 6 * * * /home/pchouinard/n8n/scripts/snapshot-vm.sh >> /home/pchouinard/recapflow-backup/snapshot.log 2>&1
#
# Schedule: 06:00 UTC daily (= 02:00 EDT / 01:00 EST, America/Toronto).
# The VM clock is Etc/UTC — all cron times are UTC. Use 06:00 UTC in summer
# (EDT, UTC-4) and change to 07:00 UTC in winter (EST, UTC-5) if strict
# local-time alignment matters; 06:00 UTC year-round is fine for a backup job.
#
# Log: appended to ~/recapflow-backup/snapshot.log (rotate manually or via logrotate later).
# Output: each run writes a new snapshot under ~/recapflow-backup/staging/<ISO-timestamp>/
#         and updates the `latest` symlink. Snapshots older than 7 are pruned.
#
# Timing rationale vs. other crons in /etc/cron.d/:
#   03:30 UTC — LanceDB snapshot (community-brain internal)
#   04:00 UTC — community-brain-lint (/etc/cron.d/community-brain-lint)
#   06:00 UTC — THIS entry (RecapFlow full-stack snapshot)
# All three are at least 90 minutes apart — no interleave risk.
#
# PATH note: snapshot-vm.sh uses docker (in /usr/bin), zstd, tar, and cp —
# all present in cron's default PATH on this Debian VM. No PATH override needed.
